00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:41,180
What?

254
00:19:41,450 --> 00:19:45,059
They won't let me wear
contact lenses, and some jerk...

255
00:19:46,660 --> 00:19:48,630
Some journalist broke my glasses
a while ago.

256
00:19:49,059 --> 00:19:50,690
So I can't really see properly.

257
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,660
It's weird, but when I can't see,

258
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:55,769
I can't hear properly either.

259
00:19:56,069 --> 00:19:58,170
I can't see your facial expression.

260
00:19:59,069 --> 00:20:01,569
It makes it hard for me to
figure out how you're feeling...

261
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:04,140
- or what you're thinking.
- So what?

262
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:15,450
You see, I can totally understand
your situation right now.

263
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:18,920
I also know that Jang Hee Jun
was the one who cheated on you.

264
00:20:19,190 --> 00:20:23,690
I totally understand how devastated
you must have felt that night.

265
00:20:24,529 --> 00:20:26,259
- So...
- It's not going to work on me.

266
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,630
I've seen you interrogate people
many times.

267
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,470
You're trying to appease me
by sweet talking to me.

268
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:38,640
Other than the police and
paramedics who were at the site,

269
00:20:38,980 --> 00:20:42,180
we couldn't find any
other person's DNA at your house.

270
00:20:42,609 --> 00:20:44,880
There were only yours and Jang
Hee Jun's.

271
00:20:45,279 --> 00:20:46,279
That was all.

272
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,390
Are you still going to deny it?

273
00:20:48,589 --> 00:20:50,390
This won't work on me either.

274
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:52,220
Exactly. It's not working at all.
Darn it.

275
00:20:54,690 --> 00:20:56,190
You're going to get charged anyway.

276
00:20:56,690 --> 00:20:58,599
The motive is clear,
and you have no alibi.

277
00:20:58,660 --> 00:21:01,099
He got killed at your house,
and there's no other suspect.

278
00:21:01,259 --> 00:21:02,329
Don't you think that's enough to
charge you?

279
00:21:02,329 --> 00:21:05,099
But I really didn't kill him.

280
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:07,140
- That doesn't even matter.
- Pardon?

281
00:21:07,299 --> 00:21:09,309
Whether you're guilty or not,
you're going to end up...

282
00:21:09,609 --> 00:21:11,509
getting the maximum sentence
allowed by law.

283
00:21:12,279 --> 00:21:13,779
That's the only way I can save
my career.

284
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:15,849
You believe me, don't you?

285
00:21:16,380 --> 00:21:19,250
I trust that you believe me.

286
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:21,950
I trust that you're on my side.
You're the only hope...

287
00:21:22,349 --> 00:21:24,019
I have right now.

288
00:21:26,759 --> 00:21:30,230
But from what I can see, there's
one person like that in your fate.

289
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,859
You'll get in huge trouble
if you cross paths with her.

290
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:37,470
That woman will completely destroy
your life.

291
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:40,970
- I've become uncivilized.
- Sorry?

292
00:21:42,339 --> 00:21:43,970
I said I've become uncivilized.

293
00:21:44,309 --> 00:21:47,079
Because of you, I'm this close to
believing what that fake monk said.

294
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:48,579
Who's that woman?

295
00:21:48,650 --> 00:21:50,750
You'll find out who she is
once you see her.

296
00:21:51,549 --> 00:21:53,119
"This must be that woman."

297
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:54,579
He said I'll find out
once I see that woman.

298
00:21:56,390 --> 00:21:57,619
Now I know who that is.

299
00:21:59,289 --> 00:22:00,319
It's...

300
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:06,930
you, Bong Hee.

301
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,940
I'm sure I've seen her somewhere.

302
00:22:16,940 --> 00:22:18,279
I've seen her in real life.

303
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:21,980
She looks extremely intimidating.

304
00:22:22,710 --> 00:22:23,880
Really?

305
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:26,049
Yes. She's really something.

306
00:22:27,579 --> 00:22:29,720
I wonder if she hired an attorney.

307
00:22:29,750 --> 00:22:31,519
The victim is the son of
District Attorney Jang.

308
00:22:31,519 --> 00:22:33,059
Who would want to defend her?

309
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:35,890
That'll only make them get on
the bad side of the prosecution.

310
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:37,130
I guess they'll use
a public defender.

311
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:39,930
They'll probably get her
one of the most incompetent...

312
00:22:39,930 --> 00:22:41,970
public defenders in this country.

313
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:45,740
What's wrong?

314
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:47,170
Ji Wook...

315
00:22:47,170 --> 00:22:49,240
Did something happen? What's up?

316
00:22:50,140 --> 00:22:51,170
He's calling me.

317
00:22:51,170 --> 00:22:52,279
(My Ji Wook)

318
00:22:52,839 --> 00:22:53,839
So?

319
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:57,349
Ji Wook's calling me.
It's been ages since he called me.

320
00:22:58,049 --> 00:22:59,049
Wait.

321
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:05,359
Hello? Hey, Ji Wook.

322
00:23:05,990 --> 00:23:06,990
Yes.

323
00:23:07,859 --> 00:23:10,460
Please do me a favor. Okay.

324
00:23:15,099 --> 00:23:17,900
I can't believe you called Mr. Ji
when you hate him so much.

325
00:23:18,369 --> 00:23:20,640
My gosh! Bugs!

326
00:23:20,740 --> 00:23:22,109
I feel like...

327
00:23:23,009 --> 00:23:24,470
there are bugs crawling on my body.

328
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:33,950
Let's go.

329
00:23:37,589 --> 00:23:38,619
(2Ha16)

330
00:23:39,319 --> 00:23:42,730
Thank goodness, I didn't
throw these glasses away.

331
00:23:42,759 --> 00:23:44,130
How did you find them?

332
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:47,329
It's not like they have legs.
I found them after a while.

333
00:23:48,430 --> 00:23:50,569
I should've gotten you new glasses
that are pretty.

334
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:54,099
I'm only going to use them for
a while. It would've been a waste.

335
00:23:54,970 --> 00:23:57,839
Of course. You're going to
get out of there soon.

336
00:24:01,109 --> 00:24:02,109
Goodness.

337
00:24:02,779 --> 00:24:05,980
By the way, these glasses
remind me of the past.

338
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:11,349
You studied so hard
with those glasses.

339
00:24:11,859 --> 00:24:14,589
And you supported me throughout
the whole journey.

340
00:24:20,299 --> 00:24:23,069
Don't you worry about me.

341
00:24:23,329 --> 00:24:25,369
It's not even my first time.
Back when your dad...

342
00:24:29,109 --> 00:24:31,240
How's the meal? Does it taste good?

343
00:24:32,140 --> 00:24:34,910
Giving massages is tiring, isn't it?

344
00:24:37,180 --> 00:24:41,079
Nonsense. Everyone lives a
tough life like I do.

345
00:24:42,549 --> 00:24:46,559
Relief patches don't cost that much.
Why do you split them like that?

346
00:24:46,619 --> 00:24:49,930
I can use them on different spots
by splitting them like this.

347
00:24:51,190 --> 00:24:54,700
By the way, how are your cellmates?
Are they nice?

348
00:24:55,769 --> 00:24:57,970
Are there any bullies?

349
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:01,769
What are you talking about?
I'm the head of the cell.

350
00:25:02,339 --> 00:25:03,769
- Really?
- Yes.

351
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:05,880
I'm the only one who got
charged with murder.

352
00:25:06,039 --> 00:25:08,279
Everyone else got charged with
theft, embezzlement,

353
00:25:08,279 --> 00:25:10,109
fraud, and gambling.

354
00:25:10,380 --> 00:25:13,519
But I got charged with murder,
so they're all scared of me.

355
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:16,849
That's great.

356
00:25:17,289 --> 00:25:18,759
Your time's up.

357
00:25:22,430 --> 00:25:25,099
Why does time fly so fast?

358
00:25:25,359 --> 00:25:28,630
Mom, you don't need to
come tomorrow. Okay?

359
00:25:28,769 --> 00:25:32,170
Don't worry about me,
and keep your head up high.

360
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:34,200
You can do it, Bong Hee.

361
00:25:35,069 --> 00:25:37,109
I can do it. I'll be off then.

362
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:38,779
You should go.

363
00:25:42,349 --> 00:25:44,410
- Bye.
- Bye, Mom.

364
00:26:02,630 --> 00:26:04,940
Why isn't she here yet?

365
00:26:10,369 --> 00:26:13,279
My goodness. My gosh.

366
00:26:13,309 --> 00:26:15,309
Are you okay?

367
00:26:17,279 --> 00:26:18,349
You hit me again.

368
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:25,519
I'm really sorry.

369
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:30,829
I'm really smart, so it's okay
if my brain cells die a little bit.

370
00:26:33,430 --> 00:26:35,170
I see. Okay.

371
00:26:40,769 --> 00:26:43,440
I got admitted as your attorney,

372
00:26:43,839 --> 00:26:47,509
so the process of admitting a public
defender will get canceled.

373
00:26:50,009 --> 00:26:51,109
I'm sorry.

374
00:26:52,150 --> 00:26:53,819
How... How did this happen?

375
00:26:56,049 --> 00:26:57,690
Your glasses...

376
00:26:58,460 --> 00:27:00,819
I'm not saying they look funny.

377
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:04,730
But they do seem to neutralize
your intimidating face.

378
00:27:04,730 --> 00:27:07,329
It's great. It's a great tactic.

379
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:09,670
- Thank you.
- I should thank you.

380
00:27:10,130 --> 00:27:11,940
Why would you thank me?

381
00:27:11,940 --> 00:27:14,269
Thanks to you, Ji Wook called me.

382
00:27:14,769 --> 00:27:15,769
Sorry?

383
00:27:15,769 --> 00:27:17,609
What kind of relationship
do you have with Ji Wook?

384
00:27:17,710 --> 00:27:21,240
He was my mentor, and now he's the
prosecutor in charge of this case.

385
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:23,750
No, not that. Is there anything
else in your relationship?

386
00:27:23,750 --> 00:27:26,849
Sir, don't you have any
questions for me?

387
00:27:26,849 --> 00:27:27,849
I do.

388
00:27:28,819 --> 00:27:30,190
Did you kill Jang Hee Jun?

389
00:27:30,650 --> 00:27:31,650
No.

390
00:27:36,490 --> 00:27:37,759
I know everything now.

391
00:27:41,230 --> 00:27:44,130
The CCTV's broken.

392
00:27:44,829 --> 00:27:48,339
This place is under reconstruction,
so there are a lot of empty houses.

393
00:27:48,839 --> 00:27:50,339
On top of that, there was
a black out that night.

394
00:27:52,109 --> 00:27:55,910
I'm sorry, but this looks like
a great place to commit murder.

395
00:27:56,049 --> 00:27:57,579
I don't know about that.

396
00:27:59,279 --> 00:28:02,890
But this place does seem
suitable for Bong Hee.

397
00:28:04,519 --> 00:28:05,720
How's the weapon search going?

398
00:28:05,859 --> 00:28:07,920
They searched the whole place,
but they haven't found anything yet.

399
00:28:08,359 --> 00:28:09,690
What about the other jurisdictions?

400
00:28:09,690 --> 00:28:12,059
I've called every police station
in Seoul and Gyeonggi Province.

401
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:15,130
I asked them to report to us if they
find a weapon that's...

402
00:28:15,130 --> 00:28:16,369
13cm in length and 3.5cm in width.

403
00:28:16,369 --> 00:28:18,400
- Okay, you did a good job.
- I did, right?

404
00:28:19,769 --> 00:28:21,470
But why are you trying so hard?

405
00:28:21,769 --> 00:28:23,509
I'm just open to possibilities.

406
00:28:23,769 --> 00:28:27,279
Like Bong Hee said, someone else
could actually be the culprit.

407
00:28:27,279 --> 00:28:28,680
Of course, that's not
for certain either.

408
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:30,480
It'd be great if that was true.

409
00:29:10,119 --> 00:29:12,660
Was it around 12:30am?

410
00:29:12,990 --> 00:29:15,660
I looked out the window
because I was feeling a bit hot.

411
00:29:16,190 --> 00:29:18,930
I couldn't see anything
because I wasn't wearing my glasses.

412
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:21,529
I just felt the cool breeze,
and that was it.

413
00:29:22,299 --> 00:29:24,369
If she witnessed something,

414
00:29:25,299 --> 00:29:26,369
but doesn't know...

415
00:29:27,099 --> 00:29:28,940
what she saw...

416
00:29:31,670 --> 00:29:32,710
That's why...

417
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,150
the witness...

418
00:29:41,349 --> 00:29:42,349
This can't be.

419
00:29:44,990 --> 00:29:46,720
Mr. Bang, you checked all the
incidents that occurred...

420
00:29:47,359 --> 00:29:50,029
around this neighborhood
on that night, right?

421
00:29:50,029 --> 00:29:51,029
Of course.

422
00:29:51,089 --> 00:29:54,529
I looked into all the sex offenders
and ex-convicts around here.

423
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,269
But I couldn't find anything.

424
00:29:57,369 --> 00:30:01,869
Can you check the residents'
whereabouts once more just in case?

425
00:30:02,109 --> 00:30:03,140
Yes, sir.

426
00:30:27,500 --> 00:30:28,730
Whoever the killer is,

427
00:30:29,269 --> 00:30:31,329
he or she definitely entered
the house and stabbed the victim.

428
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:03,500
I think I might have seen her
from somewhere.

429
00:31:06,769 --> 00:31:08,299
She has a typical face.

430
00:31:09,210 --> 00:31:10,740
But this feels a bit uncomfortable.

431
00:31:11,509 --> 00:31:13,740
Inspecting the house of someone
we know as a crime scene...

432
00:31:14,609 --> 00:31:16,210
makes me feel like
I'm prying on her.

433
00:31:17,650 --> 00:31:18,720
(No Ji Wook)

434
00:31:20,849 --> 00:31:21,920
(No Ji Wook was annoying today
as always.)

435
00:31:23,190 --> 00:31:24,250
What is that?

436
00:31:25,460 --> 00:31:26,490
It's nothing.

437
00:31:30,029 --> 00:31:32,029
Why are we shaking hands?
We can do this!

438
00:31:44,839 --> 00:31:45,839
(I can do it!)

439
00:31:48,180 --> 00:31:49,579
(No Ji Wook was annoying today
as always.)

440
00:31:50,180 --> 00:31:51,250
When you read this,

441
00:31:52,349 --> 00:31:55,319
it makes you think she might have
wanted to kill you, not Mr. Jang.

442
00:32:04,359 --> 00:32:05,430
Hello?

443
00:32:06,700 --> 00:32:07,759
Yes, this is he.

444
00:32:09,769 --> 00:32:10,769
Please go on.

445
00:32:12,099 --> 00:32:13,099
Okay.

446
00:32:24,750 --> 00:32:26,119
The murder weapon has been found.

447
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:30,750
It was found in a place that is
7km far from here.

448
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:33,059
A passerby who was taking a walk
found it and reported.

449
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:36,230
What is this?

450
00:32:36,690 --> 00:32:38,759
The length is 13cm
and the width is 3.5cm.

451
00:32:38,859 --> 00:32:41,930
The weapon fits the size
of the stab wound on Jang Hee Jun.

452
00:32:45,369 --> 00:32:47,440
It must look something like this.

453
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:50,109
That's...

454
00:32:52,809 --> 00:32:54,309
Why isn't she indicted yet?

455
00:32:57,779 --> 00:32:59,380
A further investigation
is necessary.

456
00:32:59,450 --> 00:33:03,190
We currently have no direct evidence
like the murder weapon or witnesses.

457
00:33:03,220 --> 00:33:05,960
And she hasn't
admitted to it yet either.

458
00:33:06,420 --> 00:33:07,460
The murder weapon...

459
00:33:08,890 --> 00:33:10,329
You might find it soon.

460
00:33:11,789 --> 00:33:14,059
What needs to turn up always
turns up.

461
00:33:15,430 --> 00:33:19,339
As both of us know, what's important
is that Eun Bong Hee is the culprit.

462
00:33:19,970 --> 00:33:21,000
Am I wrong?

463
00:33:24,809 --> 00:33:26,710
You said this place has been
searched multiple times, right?

464
00:33:26,809 --> 00:33:28,640
We searched here so many times.

465
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:32,009
You have no idea how many times
we did it to find the murder weapon.

466
00:33:32,579 --> 00:33:35,519
And you still found nothing,
yet this ended up in my hand.

467
00:33:36,390 --> 00:33:39,519
Plus, we might have found two.

468
00:33:39,759 --> 00:33:40,859
Well, the other one...

469
00:33:41,690 --> 00:33:43,430
Gosh, I have no idea
what's happening right now.

470
00:33:43,890 --> 00:33:45,160
Let's go to the Forensic Center.

471
00:33:45,160 --> 00:33:46,700
(Forensic Center: Collects and
analyzes crime related information.)

472
00:33:46,700 --> 00:33:48,660
I need to find out whether the blood
on these are Jang Hee Jun's.

473
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:52,069
Please run an analysis as soon as
possible. And keep it confidential.

474
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:53,940
- Confidential?
- Yes.

475
00:33:55,970 --> 00:33:58,609
This was found on the scene, so
it doesn't have to be confidential.

476
00:33:58,609 --> 00:33:59,609
But this one over here.

477
00:34:00,210 --> 00:34:04,009
It was found elsewhere,
so it must be kept confidential.

478
00:34:05,180 --> 00:34:07,619
Mr. Ji, what's your IQ?

479
00:34:08,119 --> 00:34:10,690
143. It's quite high.

480
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:11,920
Right.

481
00:34:14,989 --> 00:34:16,590
- Aren't you going to ask me?
- Sorry?

482
00:34:16,690 --> 00:34:18,059
People usually reciprocate.

483
00:34:18,159 --> 00:34:20,559
When someone says hello,
most people say it back.

484
00:34:20,559 --> 00:34:21,599
Oh, right.

485
00:34:23,130 --> 00:34:26,500
All right. My IQ is 143.
What's yours?

486
00:34:26,500 --> 00:34:27,539
It's 101.

487
00:34:30,309 --> 00:34:32,639
I passed the bar exam
with that IQ. Isn't it impressive?

488
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:35,239
Also, I used to be
an aspiring athlete.

489
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:38,780
How much effort do you think
I had to make to pass the bar exam?

490
00:34:41,420 --> 00:34:45,090
I asked myself every single day.
"Should I just quit everything..."

491
00:34:45,090 --> 00:34:47,519
"and earn money
so that I can help my family?"

492
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,690
I mean, I wasn't even confident
that I'd pass it.

493
00:34:51,329 --> 00:34:52,760
Studying was hard,

494
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:56,000
but watching my mom having
to support me was even harder.

495
00:34:56,699 --> 00:34:58,500
That's how I came this far,

496
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:02,239
but all the time and effort...

497
00:35:03,969 --> 00:35:05,579
are about to go down the drain.

498
00:35:07,739 --> 00:35:10,250
So please don't think
of defending me as a joke.

499
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:15,179
"I pity her,
so I should help her a little."

500
00:35:15,179 --> 00:35:16,550
I don't want that mindset either.

501
00:35:17,849 --> 00:35:19,559
My life depends on this,

502
00:35:21,059 --> 00:35:23,059
and my family is also at stake.

503
00:35:26,929 --> 00:35:28,800
Do we have to see each other?

