00:51:07,639 --> 00:51:08,639
Yes, Your Honor.

752
00:51:11,139 --> 00:51:12,210
The truth is...

753
00:51:13,880 --> 00:51:16,309
there was one more weapon...

754
00:51:17,309 --> 00:51:18,349
that was discovered.

755
00:51:28,889 --> 00:51:31,530
These two weapons were found
on the same day at different places.

756
00:51:36,699 --> 00:51:37,869
(Stenographer)

757
00:51:38,530 --> 00:51:42,539
Jang Hee Jun, the victim's blood
was on both of these weapons.

758
00:51:44,969 --> 00:51:46,139
If you look at this slide,

759
00:51:47,039 --> 00:51:49,710
there is a map where the other
weapon was found.

760
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:54,679
It's about 7km far
from the crime scene.

761
00:51:55,250 --> 00:51:58,889
Considering the time of death and
the response time of the ambulance,

762
00:51:58,889 --> 00:52:01,059
it's impossible for the accused
to travel this far...

763
00:52:01,219 --> 00:52:04,860
after killing the victim in order to
conceal the murder weapon.

764
00:52:07,929 --> 00:52:10,929
Either she has an accomplice who
could have disposed the weapon,

765
00:52:11,070 --> 00:52:14,199
or unless she is a super human
who can teleport,

766
00:52:15,340 --> 00:52:16,739
this is impossible.

767
00:52:16,739 --> 00:52:17,769
(Defendant)

768
00:52:17,769 --> 00:52:20,579
Then why are you submitting...

769
00:52:20,840 --> 00:52:22,909
this piece of evidence just now?

770
00:52:33,389 --> 00:52:35,119
I excluded this evidence on purpose.

771
00:52:37,530 --> 00:52:39,159
Going forward with the trial...

772
00:52:39,730 --> 00:52:42,429
was more important
than the truth to me.

773
00:52:44,030 --> 00:52:47,099
If there are two murder weapons,

774
00:52:47,599 --> 00:52:49,369
it means one of them is fabricated.

775
00:52:51,070 --> 00:52:54,340
Which means the weapons
are not admissible evidence.

776
00:52:55,679 --> 00:52:56,849
Ergo,

777
00:52:58,110 --> 00:53:00,280
according to Article 255
of the Criminal Procedure Law,

778
00:53:04,889 --> 00:53:06,050
the prosecution moves
to dismiss the charge.

779
00:53:21,469 --> 00:53:24,940
I can't understand a thing.
What's going to happen to Bong Hee?

780
00:53:25,010 --> 00:53:28,110
What is he saying?
What does that mean?

781
00:53:28,110 --> 00:53:31,409
The prosecutor dug up
his own grave,

782
00:53:32,380 --> 00:53:35,079
and he will release the defendant.

783
00:53:35,219 --> 00:53:36,219
Really?

784
00:53:36,250 --> 00:53:39,420
The prosecutor ended the case
with his own hands.

785
00:53:39,650 --> 00:53:43,989
The defendant, Eun Bong Hee,
will be released.

786
00:53:44,329 --> 00:53:47,400
So it means she can go home.

787
00:53:47,530 --> 00:53:49,760
Sir. My goodness. Thank you, sir.

788
00:53:49,760 --> 00:53:51,429
You don't have to thank me.

789
00:53:51,429 --> 00:53:52,630
Oh, right.

790
00:54:11,489 --> 00:54:12,489
- He's coming.
- There he is.

791
00:54:12,489 --> 00:54:13,489
He's coming out now.

792
00:54:13,519 --> 00:54:16,260
Isn't this an unprecedented case
where prosecution drops the charges?

793
00:54:16,260 --> 00:54:17,429
Did you obtain
the approval beforehand?

794
00:54:17,429 --> 00:54:18,559
Did you run it by the DA?

795
00:54:18,559 --> 00:54:20,530
- Isn't this act of rebellion?
- Was this settled in advance?

796
00:54:20,860 --> 00:54:22,300
- Please share a few words.
- She's here!

797
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:23,329
- She's coming out.
- Here she is.

798
00:54:23,929 --> 00:54:25,030
- How do you feel?
- How do you feel?

799
00:54:25,030 --> 00:54:26,599
- We'll hold an interview later.
- Getting your case dismissed...

800
00:54:26,599 --> 00:54:28,099
- isn't the end, don't you think?
- What are your thoughts on this?

801
00:54:28,099 --> 00:54:30,010
- Share a word with us, please.
- I'm sorry. Please move aside.

802
00:54:30,010 --> 00:54:32,170
- Tell us how you feel.
- Please share a few words.

803
00:54:32,170 --> 00:54:33,840
- Did you expect this to happen?
- Were you aware of the evidence?

804
00:54:33,909 --> 00:54:35,880
- How do you feel now?
- Hold on a second.

805
00:54:35,880 --> 00:54:37,150
- I'm sorry.
- Please tell us what you think.

806
00:54:37,409 --> 00:54:39,079
What are your thoughts on the
result?

807
00:54:39,079 --> 00:54:40,349
Tell us your thought
about the result.

808
00:55:05,239 --> 00:55:07,380
Bong Hee, let's get going.

809
00:55:07,380 --> 00:55:08,440
Let us know what you think
about the result.

810
00:55:08,440 --> 00:55:09,780
- Please answer a question.
- Tell us!

811
00:55:09,780 --> 00:55:11,250
- Tell us your thoughts!
- Please!

812
00:55:11,650 --> 00:55:13,010
Isn't this unprecedented?

813
00:56:03,530 --> 00:56:04,530
I'm fine.

814
00:56:21,449 --> 00:56:23,119
You didn't have to do that.

815
00:56:23,949 --> 00:56:24,949
I guess.

816
00:56:25,050 --> 00:56:26,389
You did that in case...

817
00:56:26,889 --> 00:56:29,159
the prosecution files
an appeal even if she's acquitted.

818
00:56:31,429 --> 00:56:32,429
I don't know.

819
00:56:36,929 --> 00:56:38,429
The prosecution won't appeal?

820
00:56:39,400 --> 00:56:42,800
When a prosecutor drops the charges,
they can't prosecute me again...

821
00:56:43,039 --> 00:56:45,409
unless they find another
piece of evidence...

822
00:56:45,409 --> 00:56:47,110
that proves me guilty.

823
00:56:47,610 --> 00:56:48,909
Put it in layman's terms.

824
00:56:50,309 --> 00:56:51,380
So it means...

825
00:56:52,380 --> 00:56:56,519
the prosecution can arrest me again
only when they find...

826
00:56:57,050 --> 00:56:59,119
a crucial piece of evidence
that points me as a murderer.

827
00:57:01,420 --> 00:57:02,960
I'm so relieved.

828
00:57:03,730 --> 00:57:04,960
That sounds about right.

829
00:57:14,099 --> 00:57:16,599
The prosecutor made
a big sacrifice for me, Mom.

830
00:57:22,079 --> 00:57:25,650
What's your relationship with her?
Why did you do that for her?

831
00:57:28,380 --> 00:57:29,420
It's fate.

832
00:57:29,920 --> 00:57:31,119
Fate?

833
00:58:01,380 --> 00:58:03,889
(Likewise)

834
00:58:05,849 --> 00:58:07,889
(Likewise)

835
00:58:54,099 --> 00:58:56,000
Your conscience disappointed me.

836
00:58:57,969 --> 00:59:00,139
I thought it'd be easy for you
to disregard the truth.

837
00:59:06,679 --> 00:59:08,150
I'm sure I'm more disappointed
than you are.

838
00:59:08,150 --> 00:59:09,280
(Prosecutor No Ji Wook)

839
00:59:10,690 --> 00:59:12,750
My justness certainly let me down.

840
00:59:23,199 --> 00:59:24,400
(Prosecutor's Oath of Office)

841
00:59:24,630 --> 00:59:26,400
(Prosecutor Code of Conduct, Follow
the principles and right paths.)

842
00:59:29,239 --> 00:59:30,239
I should go.

843
00:59:43,119 --> 00:59:45,090
Burnt and hurt by men,

844
00:59:45,489 --> 00:59:49,019
I thought I'd never be able
to fully trust anyone again.

845
00:59:56,460 --> 00:59:59,900
But I've come to trust
and like someone again.

846
01:00:01,969 --> 01:00:03,269
It's that guy.

847
01:00:04,309 --> 01:00:06,710
The man who saved me.

848
01:00:34,400 --> 01:00:37,809
(Sunho District Prosecutor's Office)

849
01:00:54,460 --> 01:00:55,489
I think that we...

850
01:00:57,030 --> 01:00:58,090
met by fate.

851
01:01:02,099 --> 01:01:03,829
I also think you're my destiny...

852
01:01:03,869 --> 01:01:04,929
An ill-fated encounter.

853
01:01:12,039 --> 01:01:13,139
So...

854
01:01:15,079 --> 01:01:16,440
let's never cross paths again.

855
01:01:36,800 --> 01:01:38,599
Dad, I gave up
the prosecutor's badge.

856
01:01:38,599 --> 01:01:40,400
I'm sorry
I couldn't become like you.

857
01:01:40,400 --> 01:01:43,099
Attorney No!
You're no longer a prosecutor.

858
01:01:43,099 --> 01:01:45,070
Welcome, No Ji Wook!

859
01:01:45,809 --> 01:01:48,539
- Get lost.
- Whenever things got stressful...

860
01:01:48,539 --> 01:01:51,280
from time to time, I took a little
break by peeking at you.

861
01:01:51,480 --> 01:01:52,980
I think I met the real culprit.

862
01:01:53,079 --> 01:01:54,349
I'll find the culprit!

863
01:01:54,349 --> 01:01:57,190
I'll become successful and make sure
to repay your kindness too!

864
01:01:57,190 --> 01:02:00,659
I'll be sure to prove to you
that we're not ill-fated.

865
01:02:02,989 --> 01:02:08,800
(Love in Trouble)
